<shortcode>01tr</shortcode>
<problem>
            <para>Before beginning its descent, a roller coaster is always pulled up the first hill to a high initial height. Work is done on the roller coaster to achieve this initial height. A coaster designer is considering three different incline angles <emphasis effect="bold">of the hill</emphasis> at which to drag the <unit_number><number>2000</number><unit>kg</unit></unit_number> car train to the top of the <unit_number><number>60</number><unit>m</unit></unit_number> high hill. In each case, the force applied to the car will be applied parallel to the hill. Her critical question is: which angle would require the least work? Analyse the data, determine the work done in each case, and answer this critical question.</para>
            <table>
              <tgroup cols="4">
                <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1"/>
                <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2"/>
                <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3"/>
                <colspec colname="c4" colnum="4"/>
                <tbody>
                  <row>
                    <entry>
